title: Egypt: Minister - Investors From World Countries Seek Operating in Suez Canal Axis
text:
Egypt/Uganda: Egypt Pile More Misery On Kobs in U-23 Qualifiers 
Investment Minister Ashraf Salman said that the ministry has received a number of letters of intent for investment in the Suez Canal axis development projects from investors from Saudi Arabia, Kuwait, United Arab Emirates, China and Italy. 
The Minister pointed out that these offers will be discussed after announcing the general plan for the Suez Canal axis development. 
He added that these letters of intent were received during the trips paid by President Abdel Fattah El Sisi to promote the Suez Canal axis development projects abroad. Egypt
